"{\"uid\": \"columbiatribune.com-story-lifestyle-2024-07-17-before-the-summer-olympics-trek-through-ancient-and-underwater-paris-74408163007\", \"noun_phrases\": [{\"sentence\": \"Editor's note: This is the first in a series of five columns revolving around the Summer Olympics in Paris.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 107, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 101, \"end\": 106, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999999386091, \"rank\": 6.11670336132543e-11, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Editor's note\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 13}, {\"ngram\": \"a series\", \"from\": 36, \"to\": 44}, {\"ngram\": \"five columns\", \"from\": 48, \"to\": 60}, {\"ngram\": \"the Summer Olympics\", \"from\": 78, \"to\": 97}]}, {\"sentence\": \"When we think of Paris, the Eiffel Tower, the Louvre, and bustling cafes likely come to mind.\", \"from\": 109, \"to\": 202, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 126, \"end\": 131, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999999386091, \"rank\": 6.11670336132543e-11, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 155, \"end\": 161, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Louvre\", \"score\": 0.9976167072888009, \"rank\": 0.0023889863650707606, \"text\": \"Louvre\", \"types\": [\"Q41176\", \"Q33506\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Louvre\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Louvre\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the Eiffel Tower\", \"from\": 133, \"to\": 149}, {\"ngram\": \"bustling cafes\", \"from\": 167, \"to\": 181}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But have you ever wondered what this famous city looked like millions of years ago?\", \"from\": 203, \"to\": 286, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"this famous city\", \"from\": 235, \"to\": 251}, {\"ngram\": \"millions\", \"from\": 264, \"to\": 272}, {\"ngram\": \"years\", \"from\": 276, \"to\": 281}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Let us take a journey through the natural history of Paris, exploring how the land was formed, what creatures once roamed here, and how it evolved into the vibrant city we know today.\", \"from\": 288, \"to\": 471, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 341, \"end\": 346, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999999386091, \"rank\": 6.11670336132543e-11, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"us\", \"from\": 292, \"to\": 294}, {\"ngram\": \"a journey\", \"from\": 300, \"to\": 309}, {\"ngram\": \"the natural history\", \"from\": 318, \"to\": 337}, {\"ngram\": \"the land\", \"from\": 362, \"to\": 370}, {\"ngram\": \"what creatures\", \"from\": 383, \"to\": 397}, {\"ngram\": \"the vibrant city\", \"from\": 440, \"to\": 456}]}, {\"sentence\": \"About 45 million years ago, during the Eocene Epoch, the area that is now Paris was dramatically different from the big city we know today.\", \"from\": 473, \"to\": 612, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 547, \"end\": 552, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999999386091, \"rank\": 6.11670336132543e-11, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the Eocene Epoch\", \"from\": 508, \"to\": 524}, {\"ngram\": \"the area\", \"from\": 526, \"to\": 534}, {\"ngram\": \"the big city\", \"from\": 585, \"to\": 597}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Instead of a city, it was a very warm shallow sea.\", \"from\": 613, \"to\": 663, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a city\", \"from\": 624, \"to\": 630}, {\"ngram\": \"a very warm shallow sea\", \"from\": 639, \"to\": 662}]}, {\"sentence\": \"This ancient sea was full of life, and was like an underwater natural city itself.\", \"from\": 664, \"to\": 746, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"This ancient sea\", \"from\": 664, \"to\": 680}, {\"ngram\": \"life\", \"from\": 693, \"to\": 697}, {\"ngram\": \"an underwater natural city\", \"from\": 712, \"to\": 738}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Diving beneath the surface were a variety of marine creatures.\", \"from\": 748, \"to\": 810, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the surface\", \"from\": 763, \"to\": 774}, {\"ngram\": \"a variety\", \"from\": 780, \"to\": 789}, {\"ngram\": \"marine creatures\", \"from\": 793, \"to\": 809}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Schools of fish darted through the water while long-necked Plesiosaurs and sharks swam through looking for prey.\", \"from\": 811, \"to\": 923, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Schools\", \"from\": 811, \"to\": 818}, {\"ngram\": \"fish\", \"from\": 822, \"to\": 826}, {\"ngram\": \"the water\", \"from\": 842, \"to\": 851}, {\"ngram\": \"long-necked Plesiosaurs\", \"from\": 858, \"to\": 881}, {\"ngram\": \"prey\", \"from\": 918, \"to\": 922}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Coral reefs, much like those found in tropical oceans today, provided shelter and food for many organisms.\", \"from\": 924, \"to\": 1030, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"tropical oceans\", \"from\": 962, \"to\": 977}, {\"ngram\": \"shelter\", \"from\": 994, \"to\": 1001}, {\"ngram\": \"food\", \"from\": 1006, \"to\": 1010}, {\"ngram\": \"many organisms\", \"from\": 1015, \"to\": 1029}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Crustaceans scurried along the sea floor, and ancient crabs and lobsters hid in the coral and rocks.\", \"from\": 1031, \"to\": 1131, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Crustaceans\", \"from\": 1031, \"to\": 1042}, {\"ngram\": \"the sea floor\", \"from\": 1058, \"to\": 1071}, {\"ngram\": \"ancient crabs\", \"from\": 1077, \"to\": 1090}, {\"ngram\": \"lobsters\", \"from\": 1095, \"to\": 1103}, {\"ngram\": \"the coral\", \"from\": 1111, \"to\": 1120}, {\"ngram\": \"rocks\", \"from\": 1125, \"to\": 1130}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Over millions of years, the remains of these marine organisms, along with sand and other sediments, settled on the sea floor.\", \"from\": 1133, \"to\": 1258, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"millions\", \"from\": 1138, \"to\": 1146}, {\"ngram\": \"years\", \"from\": 1150, \"to\": 1155}, {\"ngram\": \"the remains\", \"from\": 1157, \"to\": 1168}, {\"ngram\": \"these marine organisms\", \"from\": 1172, \"to\": 1194}, {\"ngram\": \"sand\", \"from\": 1207, \"to\": 1211}, {\"ngram\": \"other sediments\", \"from\": 1216, \"to\": 1231}, {\"ngram\": \"the sea floor\", \"from\": 1244, \"to\": 1257}]}, {\"sentence\": \"As layer after layer of sediment accumulated, the pressure from the weight above compressed them into limestone.\", \"from\": 1259, \"to\": 1371, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"layer\", \"from\": 1262, \"to\": 1267}, {\"ngram\": \"layer\", \"from\": 1274, \"to\": 1279}, {\"ngram\": \"sediment\", \"from\": 1283, \"to\": 1291}, {\"ngram\": \"the pressure\", \"from\": 1305, \"to\": 1317}, {\"ngram\": \"the weight\", \"from\": 1323, \"to\": 1333}, {\"ngram\": \"limestone\", \"from\": 1361, \"to\": 1370}]}, {\"sentence\": \"This process, known as lithification, created the foundation of what would much later become Paris.\", \"from\": 1373, \"to\": 1472, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1466, \"end\": 1471, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999999386091, \"rank\": 6.11670336132543e-11, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"This process\", \"from\": 1373, \"to\": 1385}, {\"ngram\": \"lithification\", \"from\": 1396, \"to\": 1409}, {\"ngram\": \"the foundation\", \"from\": 1419, \"to\": 1433}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Today, this limestone is not only what the city sits on, but it was used to build many of the historic buildings of Paris.\", \"from\": 1473, \"to\": 1595, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1589, \"end\": 1594, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999999386091, \"rank\": 6.11670336132543e-11, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"this limestone\", \"from\": 1480, \"to\": 1494}, {\"ngram\": \"the city\", \"from\": 1512, \"to\": 1520}, {\"ngram\": \"the historic buildings\", \"from\": 1563, \"to\": 1585}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Missouri shares a similar geologic story with Paris, as it was also built by a foundation of limestone deposited in an ancient shallow sea that covered what is now Missouri.\", \"from\": 1597, \"to\": 1770, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1597, \"end\": 1605, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Missouri_River\", \"score\": 0.9999999999504325, \"rank\": 4.9712076000632895e-11, \"text\": \"Missouri\", \"types\": [\"Q47521\", \"Q4022\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Missouri_River\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Missouri_River\"}, {\"begin\": 1643, \"end\": 1648, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999999386091, \"rank\": 6.11670336132543e-11, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 1761, \"end\": 1769, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Missouri_River\", \"score\": 0.9999999999504325, \"rank\": 4.9712076000632895e-11, \"text\": \"Missouri\", \"types\": [\"Q47521\", \"Q4022\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Missouri_River\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Missouri_River\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a similar geologic story\", \"from\": 1613, \"to\": 1637}, {\"ngram\": \"a foundation\", \"from\": 1674, \"to\": 1686}, {\"ngram\": \"limestone\", \"from\": 1690, \"to\": 1699}, {\"ngram\": \"an ancient shallow sea\", \"from\": 1713, \"to\": 1735}]}, {\"sentence\": \"This sea was home to a diverse range of marine life, including brachiopods, trilobites, and crinoids, whose remains contributed to the sediment that would eventually form limestone.\", \"from\": 1771, \"to\": 1952, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"This sea\", \"from\": 1771, \"to\": 1779}, {\"ngram\": \"home\", \"from\": 1784, \"to\": 1788}, {\"ngram\": \"a diverse range\", \"from\": 1792, \"to\": 1807}, {\"ngram\": \"marine life\", \"from\": 1811, \"to\": 1822}, {\"ngram\": \"brachiopods\", \"from\": 1834, \"to\": 1845}, {\"ngram\": \"trilobites\", \"from\": 1847, \"to\": 1857}, {\"ngram\": \"crinoids\", \"from\": 1863, \"to\": 1871}, {\"ngram\": \"whose remains\", \"from\": 1873, \"to\": 1886}, {\"ngram\": \"the sediment\", \"from\": 1902, \"to\": 1914}, {\"ngram\": \"limestone\", \"from\": 1942, \"to\": 1951}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Back to Paris - the land began to gradually rise over millions of years.\", \"from\": 1954, \"to\": 2026, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1962, \"end\": 1967, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999999386091, \"rank\": 6.11670336132543e-11, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the land\", \"from\": 1970, \"to\": 1978}, {\"ngram\": \"millions\", \"from\": 2008, \"to\": 2016}, {\"ngram\": \"years\", \"from\": 2020, \"to\": 2025}]}, {\"sentence\": \"By the time the Pleistocene Epoch rolled around about 2.6 million years ago, the landscape was dramatically different.\", \"from\": 2027, \"to\": 2145, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2043, \"end\": 2054, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Quaternary_glaciation\", \"score\": 0.9988676759741782, \"rank\": 0.00113360763